description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse looking to gain experience at UCLH? UCLH has an international reputation as a centre of clinical excellence and includes state of the art facilities such as the UCH Macmillan Cancer Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Situated in the busy West End of London, we have a lively and vibrant working atmosphere, with quick and easy transport links to all our sites&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Oncology &lt;/strong&gt;inpatient wards are looking for motivated bank nurses willing to commit to a regular line of work&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; The inpatient unit includes 2 oncology wards with a total of 42 beds, which provide a variety of treatments including:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Cytotoxic chemotherapy&lt;br /&gt;• Trial treatments&lt;br /&gt;• Biological therapies&lt;br /&gt;• Radiotherapy&lt;br /&gt;• Brachytherapy&lt;br /&gt;• Radioisotope treatments &lt;br /&gt;• Palliative care including complex symptom management end of life care&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Regular bank workers willing to commit to a minimum of 2 shifts a week will be offered a paid place on the acute oncology study day and the 3 hour Sage &amp; Thyme communications training. This will total 10.5 hours towards your F2F CDP for NMC revalidation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After a minimum of 8 shifts and following the successful competency assessments for ANTT, IV administration and CVCs you will be paid a B5+ for your continued commitment to the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If a line of work in oncology interests you please call Oncology Matron - Janet Saunders 07508 015 516, alternatively please apply directly and a member of the Bank recruitment team will contact you shortly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Bank Nurses are invaluable to us and in return for their dedication and commitment, we offer the following benefits:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work across all UCLH departments gaining invaluable skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to “Lines of Work” (guaranteed short, medium or long term shifts)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Priority of shifts over an agency worker, accommodating your availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An online self booking system that also allows you to submit timesheets electronically - “No more paper time sheets”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A designated onsite co-ordinator to offer support and introduce you to various departments within UCLH&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated recruitment team to ensure you can work as quickly as possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bookings team to ensure you work when and wherever you want to&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have 6 months NHS experience and you are looking to further your career in a hospital that has cutting edge technology, please apply online today.&lt;/p&gt;
